Gunderbooka is believed to be derived from a local Aboriginal word and is also the name of Gundabook Station.
The Darling River is the boundary between Gunderbooka and Cowper .
^ Geographical Names Board of NSW [ dead link ]

Gunderbooka County, New South Wales is one of the 141 Cadastral divisions of New South Wales . The Warrego River is the western boundary, and the Culgoa River and Darling River is the south-eastern boundary. It includes the area down to where the Warrego meets the Darling, to the north of Bourke (including North Bourke).
